article.description: Ian Baker scored 17 of his career-high 26 points in the second half as New Mexico State pulled away for a 73-53 win over UTEP on Saturday night.
article.headline: Baker, New Mexico State pull away from UTEP for 73-53 win
article.linkText: Baker, New Mexico State pull away from UTEP for 73-53 win
article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- Ian Baker scored 17 of his career-high 26 points in the second half as New Mexico State pulled away for a 73-53 win over UTEP on Saturday night. Baker hit six 3-pointers, also a career best, and had five assists for New Mexico State (6-5), which snapped a three-game skid. Pascal Siakam had 14 points and 10 rebounds while Jalyn Pennie scored a career-high 14 with eight boards. Matt Taylor added nine points and a career-best eight assists. The Aggies took a 31-30 lead into halftime and led 38-37 before back-to-back 3s by Baker sparked a 10-1 run that made it 48-38 with 13 minutes left. Omega Harris hit a 3-pointer and Lee Moore made a layup to pull UTEP (6-4) within five about 90 seconds later, but Baker scored 10 and Siakam eight as New Mexico outscored the Miners 25-10 over the final 11 minutes. Harris led UTEP with a career-high 23 points.
